            <p><add hand="#barker">The body politic "only right by accident."</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Brazoria </placeName><date when="1836-09-08">Sept. 8th- 1836</date></p>

<p><persName>Genl Austin</persName></p>

<p>Dear Sir,</p>

<p>Yours under date of [September 1 (?)] informing me of the illness of
<persName>Doctor Archer</persName> has been received&#8212;and I have sent you some good Claret
by <persName>Sergent Foot</persName> who goes via of <placeName>Columbia </placeName>I have a great many little
things which I would be glad to send you and which would add much to
your comfort but I do not know or are rather am not acquainted with the
bearer.</p>

<p>I saw <persName>Mr. Perry</persName> Two days since I believe they are all well you will
no doubt have received the returns of the Election in this Jurisdiction.</p>

<p>The <persName>body Politic</persName> is unlike Every other machine that Ever Existed, other
machines may be thrown out of order by some accident but this is only
right by accident.&#8212;</p>

<p>I have sent you Two or three <placeName>newspapers [of] New Orleans</placeName> which contain
but little. The <placeName>port of Matamoros</placeName> is opened, for provisions of all kinds,
and I have no doubt from what I can gather that an <persName>army </persName>will soon
assemble at <placeName>Matamoros </placeName>for the purpose of invading <placeName>Texas</placeName>.&#8212;</p>

<p><persName>Edmund Andrews</persName></p>

<p>[Addressed:] <persName>Genl Stephen F Austin</persName> Near <placeName>Goliad</placeName></p>



        </div1>
